@NODE ADD-1 "INTRODUCTION"

This program was designed to be used on a hard-drive system where 
access would be almost instant and there for the program can be of 
the most use.

On my 1200 I use TOOLS DAEMON by Nico François, this immensely 
useful program allows the user to add any operation to the menu 
bar of Workbench, I highly recommend it when using a hard drive. 
With this the address book program can be added to it to provide 
a quick method of access.

This program was written using SAS C V6.3 on a A1200 with 6mb 
of memory.

It has been tested on :-

           A500+
           A1200 (with & without Hard Drive or Fast Memory)
           A4000/40
		
Any problems or suggestions for improvement please contact me :-

                           JASON ROBBINS
                           33 Ingestre Road
                           Stafford
                           ST17 4DJ

Or E.MAIL

                     j.robbins@staffs.ac.uk

                     jrobbins@nyx.cs.du.edu

FUTURE IMPROVEMENTS ?

AREXX Port.

@ENDNODE

@NODE ADD-2 "RUNNING THE PROGRAM"

To run the program from workbench simply double click on the 
Address Book Icon.

In the icon you can specify SLEEP. This will make the program 
appear in it's sleep mode on startup.

To run the program from CLI simply type ADDRESS BOOK with any required 
directory path before it.

e.g. "UTILITIES:Address Book" - if the address book is in your C 
directory

If the program is to be opened in sleep mode type Address Book S.

@ENDNODE

@NODE ADD-3 " USING THE PROGRAM "
When the program is loaded you will be faced with a window looking 
like this
            ----------------------------------------- 
           |[]| Address & Telephone Book   V1.4   |[]|
           |-----------------------------------------|
           |    _________________________________    |
           | @{" <" LINK ADD-31}|_________________________________|@{"> " LINK ADD-31} |
           |    _________________________________    |
           | @{"<<" LINK ADD-31}|                                 |@{">>" LINK ADD-31} |
           |   |                                 |   |
           |   |                                 |   |
           |   |_________________________________|   | 
           |  ______   __________                    |
           | |______| |__________|  @{" DIAL  " LINK ADD-36}  @{"NO  STD" LINK ADD-37} |
           |                                         |
           | @{"                 SEARCH                " LINK ADD-34} |
           | @{"    ADD      " LINK ADD-32} @{"    EDIT     " LINK ADD-33} @{"   DELETE  " LINK ADD-35} |
           |                                         |
            -----------------------------------------

KEYBOARD SHORTCUTS

     <    = Back one name
SHIFT + < = Back one page

     >    = Forward one name
SHIFT + > = Forward one page

     D    = Dial
     N    = Dial with no STD code
     S    = Search
     A    = Add
     E    = Edit
     D    = Delete
 
@{" THE MENU " LINK ADD-38} 
@ENDNODE

@NODE ADD-31 " MOVEMENT BUTTONS "

 < - Move the address book back one name 
 > - Move the address book forward one name

 << - Move the address book back one page.
 >> - Move the address book forward one page.

The address book is sorted alphabetically by the name so the next 
to gadget move to the next letter in the book e.g. if you were 
viewing Alan Davis and pressed the »» button it would skip all 
remaining names beginning with A until it found the a name with a 
different first letter. It will then display this name. 

The «« button does the same but down the alphabet leaving you at 
the first address starting with that letter.
@ENDNODE

@NODE ADD-32 " ADD FUNCTION "
This is used to add a name to the book. When the button is release 
a window will appear looking like this

            -------------------------------------------- 
           |[]| Add Name, Address & Telephone Number |[]|
           |--------------------------------------------|
           |          ________________________________  |
           |    Name |________________________________| |
           |          ________________________________  |
           | Address |________________________________| |
           |         |________________________________| |
           |         |________________________________| |
           |          Postcode |____________|           |
           |          ______            ______________  |
           |     STD |______|   Number |______________| |
           |                   __________   __________  |
           |                  |  CANCEL  | |    O.K   | |
            --------------------------------------------

You can now enter the Name, Address & Telephone number. The Name
bar will be selected at the start and pressing RETURN or TAB will
cycle forward through the bars (SHIFT TAB will cycle in the 
reverse order).
 
These bar work the same way as standard input gadgets so clicking 
half way through a word will place the cursor at this position 
allowing for easy alteration of information. 

Once you have entered all the information press the OK button. You 
will be asked if you want to add this address to the book.
 
Clicking on NO will let you alter any of the information. Clicking 
YES will add the name to the address book and return you to the 
@{" MAIN WINDOW " LINK ADD-3} with the newly added page being displayed.
 
If you do not want to add the address to the book then click on 
the CANCEL button or CLOSE GADGET. 

If you have entered any data it will ask if you want to cancel the 
addition. Clicking NO will allow you to carry on adding the name. 
Clicking YES will return you to the @{" MAIN WINDOW " LINK ADD-3} and erase any 
entered data without adding it to the book. 

If no information was entered then the CANCEL button or Close 
Gadget will immediately return you to the @{" MAIN WINDOW " LINK ADD-3}.
@ENDNODE

@NODE ADD-33 " EDIT FUNCTION "
This button allows you to edit the currently displayed page. If 
there is no data in the book then this button will not work.

You will be presented with a identical window to the one displayed 
by the @{" ADD " LINK ADD-32} function but with current page displayed. You can now 
edit the page in the same way as in the adding of a page.

The OK, CANCEL buttons & CLOSE GADGET work in the same way as 
before, with the CANCEL button & CLOSE GADGET deleting any 
alteration you have made to leave the page as it was before 
editing began.

@{" MAIN WINDOW " LINK ADD-3}
@ENDNODE

@NODE ADD-34 " SEARCH FUNCTION "

            -------------------------------------------- 
           |[]| Search By Name Or Address            |[]|
           |--------------------------------------------|
           |                        __________          |
           |            Search For |[]| NAME  |         |
           |          ________________________________  |
           | Search  |________________________________| |
           |                        _________           |
           |                       |  CLEAR  |          |
           |                                  ________  | 
           |                                 |  AGAIN | |
           |                   __________   __________  |
           |                  |  CANCEL  | |   FIND   | |
            --------------------------------------------

The cycle gadget by "Search By" specify wether to search for a
name or address. Clicking on this will cycle between the two.

Enter a string to be found in the bar and click FIND this will 
attempt to locate the string in either the name or address fields
depending on which you specified in the Search By gadget.

The string can be any part of the name or address. The search 
routine is uncase sensitive.

e.g. if the name is in the book as David then the search string 
can be david.

If no match is found then message 

        NO (NAME/ADDRESS) FOUND WITH THAT STRING IN IT 

will be display and you can enter another name/address. 

If the name was found then you will be returned to the main window 
with the found page being displayed.

The CLEAR button will clear the search string.

The FIND button is initially by shadowed. This button is used 
after a sucessful search. If you return to search option you can 
select AGAIN.

This will try to locate the same string again in the address book 
starting at the next record.

If you press the CANCEL button you will be returned to the @{" MAIN WINDOW " LINK ADD-3}
and the search operation will be cancelled.
@ENDNODE

@NODE ADD-35 " DELETE FUNCTION "
This button is used to delete the currently displayed page. If no 
pages are in the book then this will not work.

Once the button is release you will be asked if you want to delete 
this page.

If you click the YES button then this will delete the page from 
the book. 

NOTE the page can be recovered - see @{"QUIT" LINK ADD-384}

If you click the NO button then the operation will be cancelled.
@ENDNODE

@NODE ADD-36 " DIAL FUNCTION "

This button is used to access the Tone Dialing facility of the
address book. To use this with a phone system your exchange must
be a digital exchange. 

Pressing on the Dial button will cause the program to play the 
tones for the number displayed on the current address. To get the
phone to take the tones simply hold the phone near to the speaker.
You may need to adjust the volume slightly but a moderate volume
should surfice. 

NOTE : THIS OPTION MAY NOT WORK DEPENDING ON THE QUALITY OF YOUR
       PHONE SYSTEM AND SPEAKERS.

If another program is using the audio channels (e.g. pro-tracker)
then a error will be displayed. This can only be solved by quitting
the other program as once one program has control of the audio 
channels another may not re-allocate them.

@{" MAIN WINDOW " LINK ADD-3}
@ENDNODE

@NODE ADD-37 " NO STD DIAL FUNCTION "

The No STD button will @{" DIAL " LINK ADD-36} number for local use. I.e. without the
std code required for long distance.

@{" MAIN WINDOW " LINK ADD-3}
@ENDNODE

@NODE ADD-38 " THE MENU "

 ----------------------------------------------------------------
|PROJECT                                                         |
|----------------------------------------------------------------
| @{"ABOUT" LINK ADD-5}    A?|
|------------|
| @{"SNAPSHOT" LINK ADD-381}   |
| @{"SAVE" LINK ADD-382}...  AW|
|------------|
| @{"SLEEP" LINK ADD-383}..  AS|
| @{"QUIT" LINK ADD-384}...  AQ|
 ------------

Next to each of the options is two letters these represent the 
RIGHT AMIGA key and another key. These are keyboard short-cuts. 
e.g. When the main window is highlighted you can press LEFT AMIGA 
and S to put the program to sleep. 

@{" MAIN WINDOW " LINK ADD-3}
@ENDNODE

@NODE ADD-381 " SNAPSHOT "

This will store the current location of the @{" MAIN WINDOW " LINK ADD-3} and @{" SLEEP " LINK ADD-383}
window to a config file. It will then uses these 
positions each time it is run.

@{" THE MENU " LINK ADD-38}
@ENDNODE

@NODE ADD-382 " SAVE "

This allows you to save a changed address book without having to
quit the program. 

@{" THE MENU " LINK ADD-38}   @{" MAIN WINDOW " LINK ADD-3}
@ENDNODE

@NODE ADD-383 " SLEEP "

This option puts the program to sleep and reduces the window to a 
bar that can be moved around the window.

When asleep the program can be woken by selecting the bar and 
clicking the RIGHT or MIDDLE mouse button.

To quit click on the CLOSE GADGET. The @{" QUIT " LINK ADD-384} option works the same
as before.

@{" THE MENU " LINK ADD-38}   @{" MAIN WINDOW " LINK ADD-3}
@ENDNODE

@NODE ADD-384 " QUIT "

This is one of two ways to quit the address book. The other is via 
the standard close gadget on the @{" MAIN WINDOW " LINK ADD-3} or @{" SLEEP WINDOW " LINK ADD-383}.

If you choose to quit the program and have altered the Address 
Book in any way then you will be asked if you want to save the 
address book. 

Pressing NO will not save the new address book and so you can 
recover any mistakenly deleted files. 

Pressing YES will save the book

@{" THE MENU " LINK ADD-38}
@ENDNODE

@NODE ADD-4 " KNOWN BUGS AND HISTORY "

Not so much a bug but a niggle. Does anyone know how, in v3 os, to
make the mouse pointer into a high res pointer depending on the 
user prefs.

HISTORY 

******************************************************************

V1.1 (2/1993)

This version written for all amigas with Lattice C V5.

******************************************************************

V1.2 (8/1993)

Version for V37+ (WB2.04) machines.

Improvements.

Moveable windows. 
Snaphot of windows.
Automatic selection of text entry gadgets.
Improved sorting of records.
New Look Gadgets using GadTools Library.

******************************************************************

V1.3 (10/1993)

Minor bug fixes.
Addition of tone dialing.
Amiga Guide Documentation.
Standard Install Script.

******************************************************************

V1.4 (3/1994)

Re-designed user interface.
Keyboard shortcuts.
Uses of system font and scaling interface.
 
@ENDNODE

